Reggie Belasco, as his friends called him, quivered on the floor, being as yet unaccustomed to getting shot at. Gurty stood up to examine the window and opposing wall with a bravery that verged on idiotic nonchalance. He said:
“Based on the location of the bullet hole in the wall, I’d guess dear Thomas here was the intended target, and judging by the broken pane, the shooter must have been down, around about theres, somewhere.[$ here he gestured at the precise location of the shooter, who seeing, feared his or her self to be discovered] I’m sure a sufficiently assiduous Whisk Boy[@I'm charmed and tickled that you remembered/included this. ~C] could reconstruct the shards of glass and precisely calculate—”
But he was cut short by the sound of a second gunshot and the shattering of a second pane of glass. Unfazed, he pivoted:
“This second shot, however, suggests that perhaps I am also a target (though likely of lower priority) since it nearly took my head off, and—indeed—grazed my cheek.”
Here he paused for a moment to wipe his face with his hand and look at the blood.
“You’re all mad!” Reg[$ here short for Regular, not Reginald[$Presumably when "Reg" is short for "Regular" instead of "Reginald", it's pronounced differently. Rendering this phonetically is left as an exercise for the reader. ~M]] whimpered.
Thomas was crawling across the floor to the door, which he felt would be a good idea, and the fat man followed him. Booster was continuing to babble about the room, drawing occasional fire. Thomas reached the door and sprinted down the hall to the stairs, and Big Belasco instinctively followed him, even as he thought about how that might be the most dangerous thing to do. He didn’t think about the fact that he’d been promised at least fifty-odd more hours of life, which really should have been very comforting. The two of them hippity-hopped down the stairs in the way that one descends stairs in a hurry.[$ Really, it was more in the way that two descend stairs in a hurry.] Emerging from the stairwell, and then from the hotel, they raced down the street towards the shooter.
Thomas had an idea he might be racing towards the shooter, and felt a little apprehensive about it, but the Track was the Track. Regular “Big-Belly” “The Fat Man” “Big” “Reggie” Belasco heard yet another gunshot from the direction they were heading and suddenly his instinct to follow Thomas was overridden by his instinct to flee from gunfire, and so he fled.
