GurBus up in the hotel room was getting a bit bored with monologuing to no one and getting grazed with bullets, so he decided to take a stroll down the hall and see who else was in the hotel. He was the sort to just try doors to see if they might be unlocked, or knock on doors to see who would answer. He chose a door at random, and drummed on it playfully for a second with his fists.
A middle-aged man opened the door. “May I come in?” asked Bus, starting to squat. The man was about to say, “No,” when another gunshot was heard and a bullet ruffled its target’s hair, leading him to say, “Never mind, I’ll try the other side of the hall,” as he rose again[@Is...did this middle-aged man just get shot? If Gus was in front of him and squatting, and the bullet went through his hair? ~C][@ I guess the "him" refers to "the target", but I definitely read it the other way at first before I thought about it. ~M].
