The shooter, by contrast, did not have eyes on Thomas. She had no eyes. [@ This line was conceived of by C. Altho originally it was "He" not "She", which I subsequently changed for reasons that will shortly become obvious. It was accompanied by this other written commentary by C, which on reflection I won't try to weave in more naturally, but will just include after my own annotation here ~M ❡ And have him (or her) have access to a Track-analogue geared for homicide, obviating the need for sight. ~C ❡ I almost wrote "ovulating the need for sight". How embarrassing that would have been! ~C ❡ Hmm. This would be contradicted by that one footnote where it says the assassin sees Gus gesture toward him ~C]

